{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|39","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":39,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":1,"text":"Do you know when mountain goats give birth? Have you watched the deer in labor?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":2,"text":"Can you count the months they are pregnant so you can know the time they give birth?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":3,"text":"They crouch down to give birth to their young; they deliver their newborn.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":4,"text":"Their offspring are healthy and grow up in the open field. They leave and do not return.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":5,"text":"Who set the wild donkey free? Who released the swift donkey from its harness?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":6,"text":"I made the desert its home, and the salty wasteland its dwelling.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":7,"text":"It scoffs at the noise of the village and never hears the shouts of a driver.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":8,"text":"It roams the mountains for its pastureland, searching for anything green.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":9,"text":"Would the wild ox be willing to serve you? Would it spend the night by your feeding trough?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":10,"text":"Can you hold the wild ox to a furrow by its harness? Will it plow the valleys behind you?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":11,"text":"Can you depend on it because its strength is great? Would you leave it to do your hard work?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":12,"text":"Can you trust the wild ox to harvest your grain and bring it to your threshing floor?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":13,"text":"The wings of the ostrich flap joyfully, but are her feathers and plumage like the stork’s?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":14,"text":"She abandons her eggs on the ground and lets them be warmed in the sand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":15,"text":"She forgets that a foot may crush them or that some wild animal may trample them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":16,"text":"She treats her young harshly, as if they were not her own, with no fear that her labor may have been in vain.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":17,"text":"For God has deprived her of wisdom; he has not endowed her with understanding.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":18,"text":"When she proudly spreads her wings, she laughs at the horse and its rider.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":19,"text":"Do you give strength to the horse? Do you adorn his neck with a mane?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":20,"text":"Do you make him leap like a locust? His proud snorting fills one with terror.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":21,"text":"He paws in the valley and rejoices in his strength; he charges into battle.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":22,"text":"He laughs at fear, since he is afraid of nothing; he does not run from the sword.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":23,"text":"A quiver rattles at his side, along with a flashing spear and a javelin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":24,"text":"He charges ahead with trembling rage; he cannot stand still at the sound of the ram’s horn.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":25,"text":"When the ram’s horn blasts, he snorts defiantly. He smells the battle from a distance; he hears the officers’ shouts and the battle cry.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":26,"text":"Does the hawk take flight by your understanding and spread its wings to the south?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":27,"text":"Does the eagle soar at your command and make its nest on high?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":28,"text":"It lives on a cliff where it spends the night; its stronghold is on a rocky crag.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":29,"text":"From there it searches for prey; its eyes penetrate the distance.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:39:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":39,"verse":30,"text":"Its brood gulps down blood, and where the slain are, it is there.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":39,"par